Based on my comprehensive analysis of the Shopware storefront CSS files, I can now identify the key styles that are likely conflicting with your mockup positioning. Here's a detailed summary of the potential CSS conflicts:

## CSS Styles Causing Mockup Positioning Conflicts

### **File Paths and Relevant CSS Rules:**

**1. Main Theme CSS File:**
`/var/www/html/public/theme/df557486a4363052d4729db3d1c86b46/css/all.css`

**Major Conflicts:**

#### **Body Layout Conflicts (Line 16682-16688):**
```css
body {
  -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  text-rendering: optimizeLegibility;
  display: flex;          /* ⚠️ CONFLICT: Changes body to flex container */
  min-height: 100vh;
  flex-direction: column; /* ⚠️ CONFLICT: Forces vertical flex layout */
}

main {
  flex-grow: 1;          /* ⚠️ CONFLICT: Main element grows to fill space */
}
```

#### **Container Class Conflicts (Found around line 800-820):**
```css
.container, .cms-section .boxed, .container-fluid, .container-xs, .cms-section .full-width {
  --bs-gutter-x: 40px;
  --bs-gutter-y: 0;
  width: 100%;
  padding-right: calc(var(--bs-gutter-x) * .5);  /* ⚠️ CONFLICT: 20px padding */
  padding-left: calc(var(--bs-gutter-x) * .5);   /* ⚠️ CONFLICT: 20px padding */
  margin-right: auto;     /* ⚠️ CONFLICT: Auto centering */
  margin-left: auto;      /* ⚠️ CONFLICT: Auto centering */
}

.container, .cms-section .boxed {
  max-width: 1400px;      /* ⚠️ CONFLICT: Width constraint */
}
```

**2. Bootstrap CSS File:**
`/var/www/html/vendor/shopware/storefront/Resources/app/storefront/vendor/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.css`

