}
@media (min-width: 1400px) {
  .container-xxl, .container-xl, .container-lg, .container-md, .container-sm, .container { max-width: 1320px; }
}
```

### **Your Mockup CSS (Comparison):**
`/var/www/html/custom/plugins/AndreasHurstMockup/src/Resources/public/Css/all.css`

```css
body, section {
  position: relative;
  overflow: hidden;
  height: 100vh;
  width: 100vw;
  padding: 0px;          /* ⚠️ Your styles vs Shopware's flex layout */
  margin: 0px;
}

.display {
  --top: 50%;
  --left: 50%;           /* ⚠️ Your centering vs Shopware's auto margins */
}

.display > div {
  position: absolute;
  left: var(--left);
  top: var(--top);
  max-width: 1px;
  max-height: 1px;
}
```

## **Primary Conflicts Summary:**

1. **Body Layout Conflict**: Shopware's `body { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }` vs your `body { position: relative; overflow: hidden; }`

2. **Container Auto-Centering**: Bootstrap's `margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;` interfering with your absolute positioning

3. **Container Padding**: Bootstrap's gutter system adding unwanted spacing

4. **Max-Width Constraints**: Responsive max-width rules limiting your mockup's container size

5. **Main Element Growth**: `main { flex-grow: 1; }` affecting the overall layout structure

These conflicts explain why your mockup centering isn't working as expected - the Shopware/Bootstrap styles are overriding your positioning system with their flex-based layout and auto-centering mechanisms.

